HEADWORD: Goutwort
<hw>Gout"wort`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from having been
formerly used in assuaging the pain of the gout.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A coarse umbelliferous plant of Europe
(<spn>Aegopodium Podagraria</spn>); -- called also <altname>bishop's
weed</altname>, <altname>ashweed</altname>, and <altname>herb
gerard</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gouty</ent>⟦br⟧
